# рҹҸ—пёҸ Flow Visualizer

Automatically visualize API request flows, middleware chains, and architecture in **Express**, **NestJS**, and **Next.js** projects.

![Flow Visualizer](https://img.shields.io/badge/Version-1.0.0-brightgreen)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-blue)
![Node](https://img.shields.io/badge/Node-16+-green)

## вңЁ Features

- рҹ”Қ **Automatic Code Analysis** - Scans your project and extracts routes, controllers, services, and middleware
- рҹ“Ҡ **Interactive Diagrams** - Beautiful Mermaid diagrams showing architecture flows
- рҹҺҜ **Request Flow Visualization** - See exactly how requests travel through your app
- рҹ”— **Dependency Graphs** - Understand component relationships
- рҹӣЎпёҸ **Middleware Chain** - Visualize all middleware in sequence
- рҹ’ҫ **Database Tracking** - Identify database queries and operations
- рҹ“ұ **Framework Support** - Works with Express, NestJS, and Next.js
- рҹҺЁ **Dark Theme Dashboard** - Professional, easy-to-read documentation
- вҡЎ **VS Code Integration** - Native VS Code extension

## рҹ“Ұ Installation

### As VS Code Extension

1. Install from VS Code Marketplace (coming soon)
2. Or install locally:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/DhruvSingh7077/Api-request-visualizer.git
   cd flow-visualizer
   npm install
   npm run compile
   ```
3. Press `F5` to run the extension in debug mode

### As NPM Package

```bash
npm install flow-visualizer
npx flow-visualizer analyze
```

## рҹҡҖ Quick Start

### VS Code Extension

1. Open your project in VS Code
2. Press `Ctrl+Shift+A` (or `Cmd+Shift+A` on Mac)
3. Wait for analysis to complete
4. View your architecture visualization automatically

### Command Line

```bash
# Install globally
npm install -g flow-visualizer

# Analyze your project
flow-visualizer analyze

# Or specify options
flow-visualizer analyze -p /path/to/project -o ./docs

# Export results
flow-visualizer export -f json -o analysis.json
```

## рҹҺҜ Commands

### Extension Commands

| Command | Shortcut | Description |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| Analyze Project | `Ctrl+Shift+A` | Full analysis and documentation |
| Show Request Flow | `Ctrl+Shift+F` | Display request flow diagram |
| Export Analysis | `Ctrl+Shift+E` | Export results as JSON |
| Show Overview | Menu | Architecture overview panel |
| Open Docs | Menu | Open generated documentation |

### CLI Commands

```bash
# Main analysis
flow-visualizer analyze -p ./src -o ./docs

# Initialize config
flow-visualizer init

# Serve with hot reload
flow-visualizer serve -p ./docs

# Export analysis
flow-visualizer export -f json -o data.json

# Validate project
flow-visualizer validate -p ./src
```

## рҹ“Ӣ Options

### analyze
```bash
-p, --path          Project path (default: current directory)
-o, --output        Output directory (default: .flow-visualizer)
-f, --framework     Framework (express, nestjs, nextjs, auto)
-d, --database      Include database analysis (default: true)
-m, --middleware    Include middleware visualization (default: true)
-s, --services      Include service analysis (default: true)
--no-open           Don't auto-open documentation
```

### export
```bash
-p, --path          Project path
-f, --format        Format (json, yaml, csv, markdown)
-o, --output        Output file path
```

